This paper focuses on resource allocation for mobile-edge computation offloading (MECO) systems, which involves the intersection of several computer science sub-fields. The paper deals with wireless networks and communication protocols, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with cloud computing and distributed systems, which suggests the category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with optimization and control theory, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with information theory and coding, which suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with multimedia systems and applications, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
